# UI And API State Contracts

The server owns persisted state and publishes a redacted `UIState` to the browser.

- `GET /api/state` and `/ws` both use the full `UIState` shape from `apps/server/src/state.ts`.
- WebSocket updates are fat patches: send `{ type: "state", payload: UIState }` and let the UI replace the React Query `['state']` cache.
- Do not introduce per-field WS diffs unless payload size becomes a proven problem.
- Secrets must be stripped in `apps/server/src/state.ts` before reaching the UI. Use boolean flags like `botTokenSet` or `secretSet`.
- User-generated secrets should be returned plaintext exactly once on creation.
- Browser-side types live in `apps/web/src/types.ts` and intentionally mirror only the fields the UI renders.
- UI mutations should invalidate `['state']` after success unless they directly update the cache with a complete `UIState`.
- New API routes should validate inputs, route persistent changes through `Store.update`, and preserve the loopback-only local trust model.
- Keep route handlers thin. Shared business logic belongs in packages or feature-local helpers.

## Isometric scene z-order

`iso(x, y, z)` in `apps/web/src/scenes/iso.ts` maps larger world `x + y` higher on screen, i.e. farther back. Paint order (SVG document order) must therefore be back-to-front: **descending `x + y`, with the object at world (0,0) painted last (front-most)**. Reversing this is a recurring bug — never hand-order floor-standing SVG elements.

- Route every floor-standing object through `depthSort` / `DepthSorted` in `apps/web/src/scenes/iso.ts`. An entity's `anchor` is the front corner (min x, min y) of its footprint; tiebreakers are `layer` asc → `x + y` desc → `z` asc → `key`.
- Fixed paint sequence around the sorted group: walls and floor first, then flat wall-mounted plaques (they never occlude floor objects), then the depth-sorted floor objects, then screen-space overlays (foreignObject panels, glow rects, debug grid) last.
- Groups that sort independently of each other (e.g. per-lane `DepthSorted` inside a scene-level `DepthSorted`) must occupy disjoint floor bands, or their members can interleave incorrectly.
